The Standard Adaptive Carbine Platform (ACP) allows any handgun with an accessory rail to be quickly modified into a personal defense weapon or carbine style firearm. Regardless of the brand, most pistols equipped with an accessory rail can be mounted to the ACP without the need for modification to the base gun.

ACP will accept most railed guns with barrels up to 5" in length.

This standard model allows for fast, easy conversion and works with most railed pistols, equipped with a QD sling mount.

Fabricated from solid aircraft-grade aluminum, the ACP sports M1913 rails at the 3, 6 and 9 o’clock
positions with a full-length top rail at the 12 o’clock position. Compatible accessories such as lights, red
dot sights and lasers can be mounted for additional functionality.

The ACP brings Personal Defense Weapon (PDW) features to almost any handgun.

title: For Sale:  Concealed Carry Garment
postcontent:
You are looking at a deep concealment holster/garment similar to Smart Carry (TM) and Thunderwear (TM). But why pay $20-30 MORE for their product if you don't even know it will work for you? You can own this one for far less. If, after trying it and finding out how well it works, you want a more expensive one, at least you'll be confident it's for you. BUT, I'm confident this one will work well if you like this style of carry.


This holster can be used ambidextrously and can accomodate an addtional magazine. Additionally, it incorporates an extra pocket where you can keep your ID, passport or cash. If you visit someplace where pickpockets or muggers are prevalent, this garment could be invaluable. Let the bad guy have your decoy wallet while your main documents and currency remain safe.

Holster is light weight and comfortable for the style. There is extra padding on the back to avoid any rubbing or hot spots. But, it is not bulky and will not print with loose fitting garments. I have worn mine for years and never been "made."

Some pictures of same holster are shown in black fabric. This one is khaki and the other pictures are show for demonstration purposes.

title: For Sale:  Kel Tec PF9 Great Condition Everything Factory Included. Price Firm !!
location: South OKC, Central OKC, Oklahoma City, Oklahoma
postcontent:
Have a Great Condition Kel Tec PF9 9mm up for Sale. About 1 year old. Quite possibly the best carry gun made. Super thin and light. Low count, less then 100 rounds through the gun !!

Done a few things to the gun to improve it. A Kel-Tec is meant to be "finished" by the owner for the most part. All modifications are easily reversible but I doubt you'd want to.

**This gun shoots MUCH nicer than a stock factory gun.**

- Fluff and Buffed. Gun has been broken down and deburred. Slide rails and feed ramp smoothed. Hammer surface smoothed

- Trigger straightened, softened and shortened. Biggest complaint with this gun is the trigger shape from the factory can "pinch" larger fingers. 

The shorter trigger is MUCH more controllable and softer to shoot. A stock replacement trigger is about 2 bucks from Kel-Tec.

- Hogue grip installed and trimmed. Helps suck up the recoil and improve grip on this little beast.

- +1 extended magazine bottom not only adds a round but vastly improves the gun grip.

- Extra +1 magazine. Any defensive gun needs an extra mag. It also has the +1 extension

- Sights and hammer painted orange. For some reason the white sights and my eyes did not play nicely. Orange is MUCH easier to see and get on target with. Orange hammer means it is much easier to stage the trigger (along with the shortened trigger) for fast accurate shots. Both are "painted" with orange nail polish. It's the type that doesn't need remover. Just "peels" off with a toothpick if you don't dig orange. You will though.

- Shimmed rear site. Gun was accurate but this shooter always trended a touch low with it. You may be different. Shim is just a plastic spacer that you can remove if you shoot differently than I do. I'm no marksman.

- Deburred the grip. Has some ridges on it from the factory that can hurt your hands after awhile. An hour with an emery board really smoothed things out.

Also included:

Kel-Tec plastic case

Instruction booklets

Face To Face Cash Sale and Buyer Need to Sign Bill of Sale. 
With Valid State of Oklahoma DL or State ID required to prove of age.

Need to be 18 Years Old to buy and own a firearm !!

Seller has the right Not to Sell the Firearm to anyone without Prejudice !!

Asking $350 Firm !! Because the gun has Laserlyte side Laser ($80) installed recently!!

If Interested, Please Call or Text REDACTED. I prefer Text cause I work Long hrs everyday. If you calll, Please leave yr name and phone #, I will call u back ASAP.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Best home defense sidearm IMHO. Read why.
postcontent:
Need a home defense firearm? Not the best marksman?  The long barrel taurus judge is best bet on a budget.  Notoriously known for being only useful as a snake gun, the Judge has been pushed aside as a  "movie gun".  Here's why this revolver is the hidden GEM of home defense:

-Chambered in both 410 ga AND 45 LC, the judge is versatile in non-lethal/less lethal and lethal situations. Any load smaller than 00 buck WILL NOT penetrate walls. You can make loads yourself easily anywhere from riot shells (plastic bbs), dragonfire (metal shavings/dust), to piranha shells (thumbtacks). I've considered staggering shells/rounds to expediate my EOF (escalation of force) 1= dragonfire, 2&3= less lethal shells, 4 &5= 45 LC.
-Long barrels=more energy and greater accuracy with less muzzle rise. 
-Being a SA/DA revolver, will fire as fast as you can squeeze the trigger. 
-IMHO I do not recommend this as a daily carry at all, but for me at least, this fits the bill perfectly for HD.

*6.5" Barrel
*Blued steel
*Ribber grip
*outstanding condition
